Play 2.2 application
=====================================
- Play framework implementation of the redis-backed twitter clone described in this case study http://redis.io/topics/twitter-clone
- Reactive single-page app using angularJS and websockets.
- Websocket io handled server-side by Akka actors
- Backed by redis, an in-memory key value store
- Fully nonblocking, outside of play framework and redis client internals
- Hosted on Heroku at https://clockwork-semaphore.herokuapp.com/

